The same with my description
of the Hindu structure

00:34:46.739 --> 00:34:50.219
of Angkor Wat.

00:34:50.219 --> 00:34:54.479
Let's look at some of these
components of a theory.

00:35:04.430 --> 00:35:06.500
First of all, the
notion of returning.

00:35:10.140 --> 00:35:14.730
If there is
discrimination in places

00:35:14.730 --> 00:35:18.480
which have been struck by
hierophany and therefore

00:35:18.480 --> 00:35:23.610
more significant, they would
be relatively few of them.

00:35:23.610 --> 00:35:28.020
And some would be given
particular mythological

00:35:28.020 --> 00:35:35.220
significance, and the idea of
retaining would be significant.

00:35:35.220 --> 00:35:38.010
Mumford says, in the
history of cities

00:35:38.010 --> 00:35:42.300
the magnet comes
before the container.

00:35:42.300 --> 00:35:45.780
It's an interesting
sentence to remember.

00:35:45.780 --> 00:35:49.200
Movement towards cities,
called urbanization

00:35:49.200 --> 00:35:54.060
in contemporary times,
is a reenactment

00:35:54.060 --> 00:35:59.550
of a ritual of movement
to special places--

00:35:59.550 --> 00:36:04.110
in our case is now to
secular capital cities

00:36:04.110 --> 00:36:06.375
or industrial cities
or economic cities.

00:36:12.650 --> 00:36:15.080
I will show you a
slide of Olympia

00:36:15.080 --> 00:36:19.670
in Greece, the birth
of the Olympic games,

00:36:19.670 --> 00:36:26.090
held every four years from
776 BC, a place to which

00:36:26.090 --> 00:36:30.140
we return in only four years.

00:36:30.140 --> 00:36:35.000
The contemporary
Olympic games has also

00:36:35.000 --> 00:36:38.300
maintained the cycle
of returning to a place

00:36:38.300 --> 00:36:39.800
every four years.

00:36:39.800 --> 00:36:43.910
Hitler wanted the
Olympic games after '36

00:36:43.910 --> 00:36:46.080
to be in Berlin forever.

00:36:46.080 --> 00:36:48.800
In fact, he and Speer
designed a stadium

00:36:48.800 --> 00:36:52.280
which was so large that the
Olympic rules would have to be

00:36:52.280 --> 00:36:55.925
changed to fit the stadium.

00:36:55.925 --> 00:36:59.330
But that was
Hitler's prominence.

00:36:59.330 --> 00:37:03.710
Hitler also invented the idea
of carrying the Olympic flame,

00:37:03.710 --> 00:37:09.140
which now becomes an
economic popular piece

00:37:09.140 --> 00:37:11.240
of the Olympic games.

00:37:11.240 --> 00:37:15.710
776 Olympic site was
a religious site,

00:37:15.710 --> 00:37:19.730
which priests walked around.

00:37:19.730 --> 00:37:24.500
Hitler, in trying to
manifest the assumption

00:37:24.500 --> 00:37:29.390
of the meritocracy
of the Aryan race,

00:37:29.390 --> 00:37:35.840
made special attempts to
link Germany under Hitler

00:37:35.840 --> 00:37:39.870
with Greece, with
the Athenian culture.

00:37:39.870 --> 00:37:43.160
A lot of archaeology
was sponsored

00:37:43.160 --> 00:37:48.800
by German researchers.

00:37:48.800 --> 00:37:55.370
Hitler wished to combine the
permanence and the predominance

00:37:55.370 --> 00:37:57.620
of the Aryan race.

00:37:57.620 --> 00:38:03.680
So he took the idea of
taking the flame from 776,

00:38:03.680 --> 00:38:07.880
the site of 776
BC, and taking it

00:38:07.880 --> 00:38:11.150
to that point of the earth
where the games would

00:38:11.150 --> 00:38:14.130
be held there four years.

00:38:14.130 --> 00:38:17.960
There's no other significance
to the carrying of the flame.

00:38:17.960 --> 00:38:21.830
There was no flame carried in
the original Olympic games.

00:38:21.830 --> 00:38:26.450
It's only a creation of
a manic manifestation

00:38:26.450 --> 00:38:30.230
of racial supremacy.

00:38:30.230 --> 00:38:35.950
But there are places in the
world which still venerate

00:38:35.950 --> 00:38:39.610
the idea of pilgrimage,
which is still

00:38:39.610 --> 00:38:43.630
a fundamental source
in Islam for returning

00:38:43.630 --> 00:38:51.730
to Mecca each year, places
like Varanasi and Fatima

00:38:51.730 --> 00:38:55.000
in Portugal, places that
have been sanctified

00:38:55.000 --> 00:38:56.260
in some way or other.

00:38:59.320 --> 00:39:05.170
Pilgrimage-- I'll deal with
pilgrimage in another class.

00:39:05.170 --> 00:39:08.930
Pilgrimage is a very
interesting function

00:39:08.930 --> 00:39:13.330
of lateral movement
between cities

00:39:13.330 --> 00:39:17.020
prior to the economic
significance of economic trade.

00:39:22.280 --> 00:39:24.839
Natural phenomena, number 2.

00:39:28.970 --> 00:39:34.190
Angkor Wat had a population
of, some people argue,

00:39:34.190 --> 00:39:37.070
as large as a million
people in the 14th century.

00:39:37.070 --> 00:39:42.170
I don't believe it, but
there is no way of knowing.

00:39:42.170 --> 00:39:45.980
It's significance in size
was based on the fact

00:39:45.980 --> 00:39:51.470
that it had enough water to
produce more than one crop

00:39:51.470 --> 00:39:53.120
of rice per year.

00:39:53.120 --> 00:39:57.620
Sometimes with that
amount of water,

00:39:57.620 --> 00:40:01.210
you could produce three
crops of rice per year,

00:40:01.210 --> 00:40:05.660
therefore feed an
enormous population.

00:40:05.660 --> 00:40:11.120
The plan of Angkor has
two large water systems--

00:40:11.120 --> 00:40:17.150
two are called baray, B-A-R-A-Y.
The west baray is about 7

00:40:17.150 --> 00:40:19.670
kilometers in length.

00:40:19.670 --> 00:40:23.780
The east baray, about 5.

00:40:23.780 --> 00:40:26.930
These are large bodies of water.

00:40:26.930 --> 00:40:29.750
They are precisely enclosed.

00:40:29.750 --> 00:40:34.990
The deviation of the
rectangular geometry

00:40:34.990 --> 00:40:39.330
is something like 0.01% error.

00:40:39.330 --> 00:40:43.850
They are perfectly
constructed water bodies.

00:40:43.850 --> 00:40:46.040
Between the water are towers.

00:40:52.000 --> 00:40:57.350
In religious terms,
in Hindu terms,

00:40:57.350 --> 00:41:02.570
the towers stand for
the peaks of Mount Meru,

00:41:02.570 --> 00:41:06.170
between which are seven
oceans and six continents,

00:41:06.170 --> 00:41:08.690
with Meru in the center.

00:41:08.690 --> 00:41:10.985
The lakes are the
depictions of oceans.

00:41:13.640 --> 00:41:21.380
When I visited Angkor
for the first time,

