telling in Tristes Tropiques.

01:01:41.590 --> 01:01:43.840
Levi-Strauss studies the Bororo.

01:01:43.840 --> 01:01:46.960
The Bororo are a
primitive group of people

01:01:46.960 --> 01:01:48.580
in the Mato Grosso in Brazil.

01:01:51.750 --> 01:01:54.150
Much like the Dogon
in Africa, they

01:01:54.150 --> 01:01:59.580
are a kind of naive people.

01:01:59.580 --> 01:02:04.770
The Dogon do wonderful sculpture
and put their sculpture

01:02:04.770 --> 01:02:10.110
often in places for posterity.

01:02:15.570 --> 01:02:21.880
Bororo is a system in which
the town or the village

01:02:21.880 --> 01:02:23.400
is circular.

01:02:23.400 --> 01:02:27.930
Each place has a
particular identity.

01:02:27.930 --> 01:02:30.930
And what are called moieties.

01:02:30.930 --> 01:02:35.370
There's a belief systems
are related to the place

01:02:35.370 --> 01:02:36.210
that you occupy.

01:02:38.760 --> 01:02:45.840
When the Salesian missionaries
came to missionize the Bororo,

01:02:45.840 --> 01:02:50.130
they replaced the
circular locations

01:02:50.130 --> 01:02:52.860
with rectangular constructions.

01:02:52.860 --> 01:02:58.290
The Bororo lost not only
their sense of place,

01:02:58.290 --> 01:03:00.760
but their sense of identity.

01:03:00.760 --> 01:03:09.560
So responding to the existence,
the psychic existence,

01:03:09.560 --> 01:03:13.310
was their position in place.

01:03:13.310 --> 01:03:20.860
We have elements of it today
in our religious life--

01:03:20.860 --> 01:03:24.440
those of you who
have religious lives.

01:03:24.440 --> 01:03:28.100
The position of place in
front of the altar in relation

01:03:28.100 --> 01:03:31.670
in front of the cross,
the carrying of the cross,

01:03:31.670 --> 01:03:32.240
and so on.

01:03:42.510 --> 01:03:48.780
There's a story in South African
history of the famous battle

01:03:48.780 --> 01:03:52.620
between the Zulus and
the Afrikaners in Natal

01:03:52.620 --> 01:03:58.600
in which the versions of
history are very different.

01:03:58.600 --> 01:04:01.440
The Zulus claim that
the white settlers

01:04:01.440 --> 01:04:05.250
tried to get into the
women's quarters, which

01:04:05.250 --> 01:04:09.870
are highly separate identities
in a circular system.

01:04:09.870 --> 01:04:21.790
The Afrikaners claim that the
white people were attracted

01:04:21.790 --> 01:04:27.220
to the center of this
town and were then killed,

01:04:27.220 --> 01:04:29.890
leading to the famous
Battle of Blood River,

01:04:29.890 --> 01:04:32.890
and so on and so on.

01:04:32.890 --> 01:04:35.870
Numerology, which
I won't go into,

01:04:35.870 --> 01:04:42.130
if you read the cosmology
of Chinese cities,

01:04:42.130 --> 01:04:44.530
we should have enough.

01:04:44.530 --> 01:04:52.390
The nine square system,
figures adding up vertically

01:04:52.390 --> 01:04:54.445
and horizontally
to the number 15.

01:04:57.210 --> 01:05:06.340
I'm throwing at you a lot of
little stories, fragments.

01:05:06.340 --> 01:05:14.665
There's no coherent overall text
on what I tried to describe.

01:05:18.560 --> 01:05:22.640
As for what it means
today, it's up to you to--

01:05:22.640 --> 01:05:25.700
or up to us to
make sense of this.

01:05:25.700 --> 01:05:28.890
We still have people
standing before judges.

01:05:28.890 --> 01:05:34.100
We still have a
significant night.

01:05:34.100 --> 01:05:38.540
Why build a Tower of
Babel 300 feet high?

01:05:38.540 --> 01:05:44.540
Why built the
Temple of the Moon.

01:05:44.540 --> 01:05:48.260
It's the Temple of the Moon.

01:05:48.260 --> 01:05:54.350
In Tenochtitlan on the Street
of the Dead, to the same height

01:05:54.350 --> 01:05:56.090
and put the priests on the top.

01:05:58.800 --> 01:06:03.620
There are many fragments of this
which make up an idea of a kind

01:06:03.620 --> 01:06:09.290
of city which is no longer
prevalent in our thing

01:06:09.290 --> 01:06:16.940
but still remains to the extent
when I said in our last class

01:06:16.940 --> 01:06:22.550
that we cannot under Darwinian
science explain phenomenon such

01:06:22.550 --> 01:06:25.640
as consciousness or mind.

01:06:28.610 --> 01:06:31.700
Quoting from a
recent book called

01:06:31.700 --> 01:06:39.350
Cosmos of Mind, which is a
critique of Darwinian science,

01:06:39.350 --> 01:06:42.110
"architects more than
planners, by and large,

01:06:42.110 --> 01:06:48.980
have a sense of the innate
importance of experience

01:06:48.980 --> 01:06:53.870
and believe through working at
it and every day observation

01:06:53.870 --> 01:07:02.090
and studying things you can
approximate good solutions."

01:07:02.090 --> 01:07:07.160
Whether a street in
Fifth Avenue in Manhattan

01:07:07.160 --> 01:07:11.060
has cosmic significance,
I don't know.

01:07:11.060 --> 01:07:15.750
Whether the Macy's parade
adds to that significance

01:07:15.750 --> 01:07:18.470
I don't know.

01:07:18.470 --> 01:07:22.130
I certainly know that
the parade in Madurai

01:07:22.130 --> 01:07:25.430
is different from
the Macy's parade.

01:07:25.430 --> 01:07:29.840
This Macy's parade is
not a godly phenomenon--

01:07:29.840 --> 01:07:32.360
it's the experience phenomenon.

01:07:32.360 --> 01:07:39.020
As we go on in this case,
I'll be fussing around

01:07:39.020 --> 01:07:42.750
with this
epistemological problem.

01:07:42.750 --> 01:07:45.320
How much is assumed
in our construction

01:07:45.320 --> 01:07:50.600
of the form of cities
in the rational system,

01:07:50.600 --> 01:07:54.770
which we've learned
since the Enlightenment?

01:07:54.770 --> 01:08:02.240
To what extent do we
consciously or how much

01:08:02.240 --> 01:08:06.470
do we attempt to
maintain an interest

01:08:06.470 --> 01:08:11.770
and extend in our explicit
interest in symbolic form?

01:08:14.630 --> 01:08:21.569
Symbolic form is
a powerful measure

01:08:21.569 --> 01:08:25.290
of the success of this
generation of cities.

01:08:25.290 --> 01:08:28.340
There's no question that
all the evidence suggests

01:08:28.340 --> 01:08:33.680
that our cities start with a
consciousness and expression

01:08:33.680 --> 01:08:36.990
of religious form.

01:08:36.990 --> 01:08:40.160
There is the stories.

01:08:40.160 --> 01:08:42.380
You have to believe me--

01:08:42.380 --> 01:08:43.744
no reason to.

01:08:43.744 --> 01:08:44.929
Let's look at some pictures.

01:08:48.569 --> 01:08:52.130
This is Kevin Lynch's
depiction of the sites

01:08:52.130 --> 01:08:54.920
of cities that
we're talking about,

01:08:54.920 --> 01:08:59.960
Mesoamerica around
about 1100 BC,

01:08:59.960 --> 01:09:11.210
700 BC, Egypt, well, 3500 BC,
Jericho, 8000, Sumer, 4000,

01:09:11.210 --> 01:09:19.165
Indus, 2500, Shang
China about 1700 BC.

01:09:19.165 --> 01:09:19.665
Next.

01:09:22.560 --> 01:09:29.729
OK, this is a painting of
the town of Catalhuyuk,

01:09:29.729 --> 01:09:33.720
which Jane Jacobs
claims to have been

01:09:33.720 --> 01:09:36.960
a center for the
production of obsidian

01:09:36.960 --> 01:09:42.359
and used the agricultural
area around it as servicing

01:09:42.359 --> 01:09:45.330
the industrial function.

01:09:45.330 --> 01:09:48.660
The curious thing about
another depiction,

01:09:48.660 --> 01:09:52.470
which is on the other slide,
is that there is hardly

01:09:52.470 --> 01:09:55.350
any public space at all.

01:09:55.350 --> 01:10:01.290
These are obviously alleys from
one group of houses to another.

01:10:01.290 --> 01:10:02.050
Any questions?

01:10:02.050 --> 01:10:04.380
AUDIENCE: What's the
name of the [INAUDIBLE]??

01:10:04.380 --> 01:10:06.000
JULIAN BEINART: Catalhuyuk--

01:10:06.000 --> 01:10:12.700
C-A-T-A-L-H-U-Y-U-K.
It's in Anatolia.

01:10:15.480 --> 01:10:18.060
I don't know whether
it's in Iraq or Turkey.

01:10:18.060 --> 01:10:19.500
AUDIENCE: It's in Turkey.

01:10:19.500 --> 01:10:21.390
JULIAN BEINART: It's in Turkey.

01:10:21.390 --> 01:10:23.845
Catalhuyuk is Turkish, isn't it.

01:10:23.845 --> 01:10:26.280
AUDIENCE: There is a book by
Bill Bryson called At Home

01:10:26.280 --> 01:10:28.140
where he talks
about the ceilings

01:10:28.140 --> 01:10:30.000
and how peculiar
are the entrances

01:10:30.000 --> 01:10:32.160
and exits between buildings.

01:10:32.160 --> 01:10:33.660
How is that
reflected in the map?

01:10:33.660 --> 01:10:34.350
I'm trying to--

01:10:34.350 --> 01:10:36.250
JULIAN BEINART: I don't know.

01:10:36.250 --> 01:10:42.510
These maps, like the map
in just outside Oman,

01:10:42.510 --> 01:10:49.440
the first map of Jerusalem,
are very abstract depictions.

01:10:49.440 --> 01:10:50.520
This is a wall painting.

01:10:50.520 --> 01:10:52.041
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE]

01:10:52.041 --> 01:10:57.360
JULIAN BEINART: And the
other one is an abstraction.

01:10:57.360 --> 01:11:01.350
I would place very little
faith in the observations

01:11:01.350 --> 01:11:05.310
of these towns.

01:11:05.310 --> 01:11:08.570
Archaeology is
safer, and I don't

01:11:08.570 --> 01:11:11.550
know how much archaeological
investigation has

01:11:11.550 --> 01:11:13.445
been done at Catalhuyuk.

01:11:13.445 --> 01:11:15.734
AUDIENCE: That's why
he talks about double

01:11:15.734 --> 01:11:20.390
spaced in between and
a [INAUDIBLE] grid.

01:11:20.390 --> 01:11:23.130
JULIAN BEINART: I don't
think it's Jane Jacobs,

01:11:23.130 --> 01:11:25.600
but somebody has
spoken about the roofs

01:11:25.600 --> 01:11:30.330
as being planes of utility.

01:11:30.330 --> 01:11:32.100
I don't think there's
much to be gained.

01:11:32.100 --> 01:11:34.110
It looks like a
contemporary drawing

01:11:34.110 --> 01:11:36.670
for a squatter settlement.

01:11:36.670 --> 01:11:37.170
Next.

01:11:40.350 --> 01:11:44.430
Returning to particular place.

01:11:44.430 --> 01:11:48.360
Banaras is on the left,
Kaaba on the right--

01:11:48.360 --> 01:11:54.935
an annual pilgrimage,
an every day pilgrimage.

01:11:54.935 --> 01:11:55.435
Next.

01:11:58.150 --> 01:12:05.600
Catalhuyuk-- the
notion that the water

01:12:05.600 --> 01:12:15.190
is the replication of the
ocean and the vertical building

01:12:15.190 --> 01:12:19.465
the depiction of a mountain.

01:12:19.465 --> 01:12:22.990
Mircea Eliade often talks
about mountains and cities

01:12:22.990 --> 01:12:28.160
as being center in this
kind of cosmic model.

01:12:28.160 --> 01:12:28.660
Next.

01:12:35.800 --> 01:12:37.960
One of the reasons
for the towers

01:12:37.960 --> 01:12:45.940
is because people
have no capacity

01:12:45.940 --> 01:12:49.705
to span any large distance, so
the distances are very small.

01:12:53.230 --> 01:12:58.520
Here is a parade of stone
figures on a sports field,

01:12:58.520 --> 01:12:59.740
where it's just behind this.

01:12:59.740 --> 01:13:01.900
The royal palace
doesn't exist anymore

01:13:01.900 --> 01:13:03.590
because it's built out of wood.

01:13:03.590 --> 01:13:04.090
Next.

01:13:09.140 --> 01:13:14.835
The phenomenon, and
this is Chichen Itza.

01:13:14.835 --> 01:13:15.335
Next.

01:13:21.700 --> 01:13:32.980
Chichen Itza, Masada, one
of Herod's vacation homes

01:13:32.980 --> 01:13:36.400
built on the side of the hill.

01:13:36.400 --> 01:13:41.650
Again, the notion of
building on top of something.

01:13:41.650 --> 01:13:46.690
The Romans finally
conquered Masada

01:13:46.690 --> 01:13:51.905
by building a earth
bridge to the top.

01:13:51.905 --> 01:13:52.405
Next.

01:13:57.190 --> 01:13:59.800
A depiction of
the Babylon tower.

01:14:02.710 --> 01:14:05.080
Not a very good one.

01:14:05.080 --> 01:14:09.250
And the mixture of
astronomy and religion

01:14:09.250 --> 01:14:13.420
in the case of Tenochtitlan.

01:14:13.420 --> 01:14:16.955
Equinox sunrise over
the Templo Mayor.

01:14:16.955 --> 01:14:17.455
Next.

01:14:21.320 --> 01:14:23.795
Here's the city of the Dipper.

01:14:23.795 --> 01:14:27.980
The constellations Ursa Major
and Ursa Minor superimposed

01:14:27.980 --> 01:14:31.400
in the plan of Han
Dynasty, Chang'an.

01:14:31.400 --> 01:14:35.510
The popular belief of subsequent
generations that the city was

01:14:35.510 --> 01:14:37.790
consciously designed
to this pattern

01:14:37.790 --> 01:14:41.570
is unsupported by any
independent event,

01:14:41.570 --> 01:14:44.990
nor do the positions
of the imperial palaces

01:14:44.990 --> 01:14:51.320
coincide with that of the
pulse star, and so and so.

01:14:51.320 --> 01:14:54.680
There's some doubt about
this, but it's a nice drawing.

01:15:00.060 --> 01:15:00.560
Next.

01:15:06.800 --> 01:15:10.030
The astronomical
observatory in Chichen Itza.

01:15:17.720 --> 01:15:21.050
A temple town in Southern India.

01:15:21.050 --> 01:15:24.800
Now in each of these
vertical constructions

01:15:24.800 --> 01:15:30.130
is not an astronomical
tower, but there's

01:15:30.130 --> 01:15:34.850
a regularity of the vertical
phenomenon throughout the town

01:15:34.850 --> 01:15:36.735
depicting something or other.

01:15:36.735 --> 01:15:37.235
Next.

01:15:41.860 --> 01:15:46.330
a gnomon, a tool
used by the Romans

01:15:46.330 --> 01:15:49.480
for finding a propitious site.

01:15:49.480 --> 01:15:54.040
And the geomancer's an
astrobiological instrument

01:15:54.040 --> 01:15:57.530
for choosing the right site.

01:15:57.530 --> 01:15:58.030
Next.

01:16:01.510 --> 01:16:07.240
Chinchiri in Anatolia.

01:16:07.240 --> 01:16:09.610
Interesting, the first town--

01:16:09.610 --> 01:16:14.470
settlement is fortified
with a wall that

01:16:14.470 --> 01:16:22.090
is small that surrounds the
town as intimately as possible.

01:16:22.090 --> 01:16:25.450
When the town is
economically successful,

01:16:25.450 --> 01:16:30.160
it builds itself in the
first century before Christ

01:16:30.160 --> 01:16:33.370
a surrounding wall
which is based

01:16:33.370 --> 01:16:42.650
on a superior geometry, a
perfect geometry, a geometry

01:16:42.650 --> 01:16:48.020
which can be associated
with centrality,

01:16:48.020 --> 01:16:53.450
with permanent symbolic
enclosure of high order

01:16:53.450 --> 01:16:54.650
and so on.

01:16:54.650 --> 01:16:57.830
Here the town of [INAUDIBLE]
in the 1st century BC.

01:17:01.610 --> 01:17:04.640
It used to be in the
south of the USSR--

01:17:04.640 --> 01:17:07.730
I don't know where it is now--

01:17:07.730 --> 01:17:11.470
which has an
astronomical center.

01:17:11.470 --> 01:17:15.980
It has astronomical
observation site in the center.

01:17:15.980 --> 01:17:23.295
And the town follows the
pattern as it moves outwards.

01:17:23.295 --> 01:17:23.795
Next.

01:17:28.500 --> 01:17:31.500
The town of Edfu on the Nile.

01:17:34.200 --> 01:17:35.565
Peculiar.

01:17:35.565 --> 01:17:42.180
A marvelous conjunction
of light and shadow

01:17:42.180 --> 01:17:45.675
in the marking of
a special place.

01:17:50.100 --> 01:17:51.600
Edfu is the town.

01:17:51.600 --> 01:17:53.343
It's a small town on
the banks of the--

01:17:53.343 --> 01:17:54.260
AUDIENCE: Of the Nile.

01:17:54.260 --> 01:17:56.040
JULIAN BEINART: But
you have replications

01:17:56.040 --> 01:17:59.970
of this in Luxor and
in Karnak and so on.

01:18:03.150 --> 01:18:08.580
I chose that one because I
happen to photograph it myself

01:18:08.580 --> 01:18:13.290
and I was still struck
by the conjunction

01:18:13.290 --> 01:18:16.740
of the positive light in
the form of the towers.

01:18:19.860 --> 01:18:24.520
Here's a typical
perfect Chinese town.

01:18:27.570 --> 01:18:31.200
The emperor is in
position number 1.

01:18:31.200 --> 01:18:37.230
The subsequent position's
in 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8.

01:18:37.230 --> 01:18:41.310
But the town is symmetrically
divided between right and left.

01:18:41.310 --> 01:18:45.570
There's a color for the right,
there's a color for the left.

01:18:45.570 --> 01:18:49.080
This is a town which is
perfectly controlled.

01:18:49.080 --> 01:18:52.320
And its form is
a pristine object

01:18:52.320 --> 01:18:58.090
for depicting symbolic
security and actual security.

01:18:58.090 --> 01:18:58.590
Next.

01:19:03.120 --> 01:19:09.130
Jerusalem is the head
of the three continents.

01:19:09.130 --> 01:19:12.600
The Temple Mount, which I will
describe in much greater detail

01:19:12.600 --> 01:19:13.975
as we go on in this class.

01:19:13.975 --> 01:19:14.475
Next.

01:19:19.400 --> 01:19:22.760
Oh, here we've gone out again.

01:19:28.390 --> 01:19:32.680
Those are the formation seen
from the sky in Glastonbury

01:19:32.680 --> 01:19:33.755
and Dorset.

01:19:33.755 --> 01:19:34.255
Next.

01:19:38.670 --> 01:19:43.540
The map of Mexico City and
the actual first settlement.

01:19:43.540 --> 01:19:44.040
Next.

01:19:49.635 --> 01:19:56.540
The moiety town of the
Bororo, the position

01:19:56.540 --> 01:20:01.370
of the clan system, and
moiety A and moiety B,

01:20:01.370 --> 01:20:04.800
specifying the
significance of place.

01:20:04.800 --> 01:20:07.580
Place is not arbitrary.

01:20:07.580 --> 01:20:10.810
Place is connected to
fundamental existence.

01:20:10.810 --> 01:20:17.120
And here in the
town in Cameroon we

01:20:17.120 --> 01:20:23.630
have a similar disposition of
man, wife, man, man, man, man,

01:20:23.630 --> 01:20:27.800
man, man, wife, wife,
wife, and so on.

01:20:27.800 --> 01:20:29.540
Not to be mixed up.

01:20:29.540 --> 01:20:31.790
No cohabitation.

01:20:31.790 --> 01:20:32.290
Next.

01:20:37.960 --> 01:20:39.430
The depiction of place.

01:20:39.430 --> 01:20:42.610
This is the Gate
of Heavenly Peace,

01:20:42.610 --> 01:20:48.940
the marker of the distinction
between the whole Heavenly

01:20:48.940 --> 01:20:59.650
City and the Sacred City, marked
here by a more recent emperor.

01:20:59.650 --> 01:21:05.450
And here are the
location of the Mausoleum

01:21:05.450 --> 01:21:11.710
to Mao on Tiananmen Square,
bereft of any disposition

01:21:11.710 --> 01:21:15.190
of location which
is fundamentally wed

01:21:15.190 --> 01:21:19.270
into the system of the town.

01:21:19.270 --> 01:21:21.490
It is anywhere.

01:21:21.490 --> 01:21:28.550
It looks as if it could be
anywhere, and it doesn't.

01:21:28.550 --> 01:21:31.310
The strength of that
pattern on the left

01:21:31.310 --> 01:21:37.328
is infinitely larger
than the strength--

01:21:37.328 --> 01:21:41.360
the construction of
the right is not wed,

01:21:41.360 --> 01:21:47.720
is not bred into the large
identity of the city.

01:21:47.720 --> 01:21:50.010
Next.

01:21:50.010 --> 01:21:52.760
It could be anywhere.

01:21:52.760 --> 01:21:54.860
Let's just pass this.

01:21:54.860 --> 01:21:57.310
This is a feng shui problem.

01:21:57.310 --> 01:21:59.930
Next.

01:21:59.930 --> 01:22:03.860
Depictions of the
system of approach

01:22:03.860 --> 01:22:09.560
to the central imperial
position in the city.

01:22:09.560 --> 01:22:13.040
Here are the idea
of a set of boxes,

01:22:13.040 --> 01:22:16.725
revealing more as you
go into the system.

01:22:16.725 --> 01:22:17.225
Next.

01:22:20.410 --> 01:22:25.270
The mandala, the central
premise of the Indian system.

01:22:28.030 --> 01:22:35.170
A depiction of the body
of the Brahma in a system

01:22:35.170 --> 01:22:38.860
of subdivision of land here.

01:22:45.878 --> 01:22:49.630
The Hindu religion
